(88926, "Armando Iannucci", 2, "1963-11-28", NULL, "Armando Giovanni Iannucci (born 28 November 1963) is a Scottish-Italian comedian, satirist, writer, director, performer and radio producer. Born in Glasgow, he studied at Oxford University and left graduate work on a PhD about John Milton to pursue a career in comedy.

